            <div type="edition" xml:space="preserve"><head>Text</head><ab><lb n="1"/>
                <supplied reason="lost">Pr</supplied>o <supplied reason="lost"><expan><abbr>sal</abbr><ex>ute</ex></expan></supplied> <lb n="2"/><supplied reason="lost"><expan><abbr>Imp</abbr><ex>eratoris</ex></expan> Caesaris <expan><abbr>T</abbr><ex>iti</ex></expan> Aeli H</supplied>adria<supplied reason="lost">ni <expan><abbr>Aug</abbr><ex>usti</ex></expan> et</supplied> <lb n="3"/><supplied reason="lost"><expan><abbr>Imp</abbr><ex>eratoris</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>T</abbr><ex>iti</ex></expan> Aeli Caes</supplied>aris A<supplied reason="lost">ntonini</supplied> <lb n="4"/><supplied reason="lost"><expan><abbr>I</abbr><ex>ovi</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>O</abbr><ex>ptimo</ex></expan></supplied> <expan><abbr>M</abbr><ex>aximo</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>P</abbr><ex>annoniae</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>s</abbr><ex>uperioris</ex></expan> <supplied reason="lost">exercitus</supplied>
            </ab></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Fragment einer Tafel. Reste von roter Farbe in den Buchstaben. Apices. In Z. 1 noch ein winziger Teil vom unteren Bogen des O; am Ende von Z. 2 noch der obere Ansatz und die aufsteigende Schräghaste des A zu erkennen. Datierung: zwischen 25.2.138 (Adoption des Antoninus Pius durch Hadrian) und 10.7.138 (Tod des Hadrian / dies imperii des Antoninus Pius).</p>
            </div>
